name: Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star Pokemon Pikachu (TD)
Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star Pokemon Poke Ball
story: The Pokemon x Converse Chuck Taylor All Star High ‘Poke Ball’ celebrates 25 years of the iconic gaming franchise. An all-over Pokemon print is applied to the white canvas upper, lined in crimson textile and accented with a molded Poke Ball patch on the lateral ankle. Standard Chuck details remain intact, including a rubber toe cap, a circular All Star patch, and winged stitching atop the tongue. The high-top is mounted on a white rubber midsole with black pinstripe detailing and a custom Poke Ball license plate.

name: Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star Pokemon First Partners (TD)
Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star Pokemon First Partners (PS)
Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star Pokemon Jigglypuff (TD)
Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star Pokemon First Partners
Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Dark Iris'
story: The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Dark Iris’ brings a revitalized color palette to the hardwood classic that introduced visible Air cushioning to the Jordan franchise. The sneaker utilizes a white tumbled leather upper with signature elephant print overlays in a dark grey finish. Violet accents make their way to the eyelets, perforated collar and the rear of the polyurethane midsole. Jumpman branding hits adorn the leather tongue and molded heel overlay. Underfoot, a grey rubber outsole provides durable traction.

name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Stage Haze
Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Infrared'
story: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Infrared’ features distinctive color blocking that recalls the ‘Green Glow’ AJ4 release from 2013. The upper is crafted from smooth nubuck in a charcoal finish. A lighter shade of grey distinguishes the forefoot overlay, while black accents land on the quarter panel netting, structural wings and Jumpman-branded heel tab. The sneaker’s titular hue lights up the woven tongue tag and a quartet of molded eyelets. A polyurethane midsole packs visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel for a smooth ride.

name: Air Jordan 5 'Green Bean'
story: The 2022 edition of the Air Jordan 5 ‘Green Bean’ brings back a distinctive two-tone colorway initially released in 2006. Like the original, the mid-top carries a light grey nubuck upper entirely coated in a reflective finish. Bright green accents make their way to the interior lining and the embroidered Jumpman logo that decorate the heel and tongue. The vivid hue is repeated on the shark-tooth detailing that enlivens the dark grey polyurethane midsole. Underfoot, a translucent herringbone-tread rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

name: A Ma Maniére x Air Jordan 2 Retro SP
story: The A Ma Maniére x Air Jordan 2 Retro SP reunites the Atlanta-based retailer with Jordan Brand for collaboration no. 3. This elevated take on the AJ2 showcases an off-white cracked leather upper with burgundy piping and a translucent heel counter that extends into the midfoot. ‘Maniére’ is stamped in white lettering on the burgundy leather heel tab. Contrasting black accents settle on the laces, quilted interior lining and tongue, featuring snakeskin detailing and a retro Wings logo. The black snakeskin motif is repeated on the midsole — an exotic touch that nods to the OG Air Jordan 2 from 1986, which was made in Italy and featured a subtle reptilian texture on the leather upper.

name: Union LA x Air Jordan 2 Retro SP 'Rattan'
Nike Dunk High CLOT Metallic Silver
Air Jordan 9 Retro 'Particle Grey'
story: The Air Jordan 9 Retro ‘Particle Grey’ delivers a neutral colorway of the ‘90s model that originally released during MJ’s first retirement from basketball. The retro silhouette is updated with a breathable black textile upper, secured with speed laces and accented with tonal stitch detailing. A nubuck mudguard in a neutral grey finish wraps around the heel and extends up the mid-cut collar. Contrasting hits of crimson land on the sneaker’s branding elements, including an Air Jordan tongue tag and a molded Jumpman emblem at the heel. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a matte grey polyurethane midsole with encapsulated Air-sole units in the forefoot and heel.

name: Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Del Sol'
story: The Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘Del Sol’ combines sunny accents with OG-inspired color blocking and materials. The mid-top carries a white leather upper with dimpled overlays in matching white tumbled leather. A crimson Jumpman logo graces the tongue, while a green-tinged holographic cat eye adorns the lateral ankle. Yellow synthetic suede wraps the midfoot, heel, and lightweight Phylon midsole, fitted with Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot and heel. Underfoot, the black panther-paw outsole features herringbone rubber pods and a carbon fiber shank plate.

name: Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Zen Master'
story: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Zen Master’ features a unique design that pays tribute to Phil Jackson, the Chicago Bulls head coach who helmed the team’s six championship runs with Michael Jordan during the ‘90s. The classic silhouette makes use of a textile upper in a swirling mix of pink, purple and blue — a tie dye-like effect that nods to Jackson’s ‘Zen Master’ persona. A black woven tongue features Flight branding and a scarlet Jumpman icon, while a translucent TPU heel tab displays a raised Jumpman logo in black. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a polyurethane midsole with a visible Air-sole unit in the heel.

name: Blaze of Glory 'The Never Worn'
story: The PUMA Blaze of Glory ‘The Never Worn’ dresses the ‘90s runner with retro-aged materials, complete with visible glue stains and abrasions for an aged aesthetic. The sneaker features a black mesh upper with tonal suede overlays, grey perforated suede inserts and a glossy TPU cage integrated into the lacing system. Green zigzag stitching and a matching green heel tab deliver contrasting pops of color. A vintage pre-yellowed finish is applied to a lightweight EVA midsole with PUMA’s Trinomic cushioning technology.

name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Rebellionaire
story: The Air Jordan 1 High OG ‘Rebellionaire’ showcases a unique design that ties into the shoe’s mythic ‘Banned’ narrative, wherein Michael Jordan incurred a $5,000 fine each time the rookie wore his signature black and red kicks on the court — a violation of the NBA’s uniform dress code at the time. The iconic high-top features a leather upper finished in two-tone color blocking reminiscent of the OG ‘Shadow’ colorway. Unique details include the ‘Banned’ AJ1’s red ‘X’ on the heel, along with an all-over print that spells out ‘They Can’t Stop You From Wearing Them,’ which paraphrases a line from an original Air Jordan 1 TV commercial from 1985.

name: DC Comics x Cali Star Little Kid 'Wonder Woman'
DC Comics x Cali Star Jr 'Wonder Woman'
Jordan 6 Retro UNC White
story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘UNC Home’ features a familiar color combination that pays homage to MJ’s alma mater. The iconic silhouette carries a white leather upper with nubuck underlays in University Blue. Contrasting navy accents make their way to the molded TPU heel tab, textile collar lining and polyurethane midsole, the latter enhanced with visible Air-sole cushioning. Reflective perforations provide added visibility in low-light conditions, while a woven jock tag at the heel nods to the shoe’s varsity athletics theme.

name: Rich Mnisi x Wmns Superstar OT Tech 'South African City Life'
Rich Mnisi x Wmns UltraBoost 22 'South African City Life'
Jordan Why Not Zer0.5 Childhood
story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.5 ‘Childhood’ updates Russell Westbrook’s signature shoe with a collision of bright colors, resulting in a fragmented design that nods to the distinct personalities of the athlete’s three children. The lavender-hued textile upper is reinforced with contrasting black synthetic overlays and a matching black heel counter outlined in Bright Crimson. The latter component works with aqua-colored webbing eyelets and an internal padded collar to fully secure the foot. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a sculpted foam midsole with a large-volume Zoom Air nestled under the forefoot.

name: Rich Mnisi x Wmns Forum Mid 'South African City Life'
Rich Mnisi x Wmns X9000L4 'South African City Life'
Minecraft x Suede 'Grass Block'
story: The Minecraft x PUMA Suede ‘Grass Block’ celebrates the popular sandbox video game with lush earth tones inspired by the plains, one of the game’s most common biomes. Pixelated detailing is applied to the brown suede upper and green leather Formstrip, which is layered over a second blue Formstrip on the sneaker’s lateral side. A creeper graphic embellishes the woven tongue tag, while the custom sockliner displays dual PUMA and Minecraft branding. A durable white rubber cupsole anchors the retro silhouette.

name: Rich Mnisi x Wmns ZX Wavian 'South African City Life'
Jordan 1 Retro High OG Brotherhood
story: The Air Jordan 1 High Retro OG ‘Brotherhood’ features a vibrant color scheme inspired by Omega Psi Phi, the fraternity that Michael Jordan joined as a student at the University of North Carolina. The upper combines a white leather quarter panel with nubuck overlays in Light Bordeaux. A leather toe box in University Gold is matched by wraparound leather overlays at the collar and heel. A leather Nike Air tag decorates the nylon tongue, while a classic Wings logo is stamped on the lateral ankle. Supporting the high-top is a rubber cupsole with an Air-sole heel unit encapsulated in lightweight polyurethane.

name: Jordan 1 Mid Coconut Milk (W)
story: The women’s Air Jordan 1 Mid ‘Coconut Milk’ highlights neutral tones on a familiar silhouette modeled after the 1985 original. The leather upper combines a clean white base with cream-colored overlays and a black signature Swoosh. Additional branding elements include a woven Jumpman tongue tag and a retro Wings logo stamped on the lateral ankle. The mid-top rides on a traditional rubber cupsole, featuring encapsulated Air-sole cushioning under the heel.

name: Jordan 9 Retro Chile Red
story: The Air Jordan 9 Retro ‘Chile Red’ features a saturated design that recalls the ‘Motorboat Jones’ colorway from 2012. Stitched crimson textile is utilized on the upper, secured with a speed lacing system and bolstered with tonal patent leather along the mudguard, collar and heel. Contrasting black accents land on an Air Jordan tongue tag, molded eyelets and a prominent pull loop at the heel. The sneaker rides on a glossy red polyurethane midsole, enhanced with encapsulated Air-sole units in the forefoot and heel.

name: Jordan 3 Retro Cardinal Red
story: The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Cardinal Red’ showcases a distinctive palette influenced by an OG colorway of the Air Jordan 7. The sneaker’s titular hue appears on the collar lining, molded eyelets, and raised Jumpman branding at the heel, all of which are contrasted by a white tumbled leather upper. A second Jumpman icon adorns the tongue in orange embroidery, while the 3’s signature elephant print overlays reinforce the forefoot and heel. The mid-top is mounted on a two-tone polyurethane midsole with a visible Air-sole unit nestled under the heel.

name: Air Jordan 3 Retro TD 'Cardinal Red'
story: The Air Jordan 3 Retro TD ‘Cardinal Red’ delivers a scaled-down version of the classic silhouette, featuring a white tumbled leather upper with a familiar accent color borrowed from the Air Jordan 7. The rich crimson hue appears on the collar lining, cushioned foam midsole, and Jumpman heel logo. Grey elephant overlays maintain the sneaker’s OG-inspired aesthetic. Atop the tongue, an orange embroidered Jumpman provides a contrasting pop of color.

name: Air Jordan 3 Retro PS 'Cardinal Red'
story: Offered in little kid sizing, the Air Jordan 3 Retro PS ‘Cardinal Red’ showcases a familiar accent color borrowed from the Air Jordan 7. The dark scarlet hue appears on the upper eyelets, collar lining, and Jumpman heel logo, allowing the details to stand out against a white tumbled leather backdrop. Grey elephant print overlays maintain the Air Jordan 3’s iconic aesthetic. Lightweight cushioning arrives by way of a two-tone foam midsole, supported underfoot by a durable grey rubber outsole.

name: Air Jordan 3 Retro GS 'Cardinal Red'
story: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 3 Retro GS ‘Cardinal Red’ takes inspiration from an OG colorway of the Air Jordan 7. The mid-top carries a white tumbled leather upper with dark red accents on the eyelets, collar lining, and the raised Jumpman logo that adorns the heel. Additional Jumpman branding decorates the tongue in orange embroidery. The 3’s signature elephant print lands on the eyestay and forefoot and heel overlay. Underpinning the mid-top is a white and red polyurethane midsole with visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel.

name: Jordan 12 Retro Playoffs (2022)
story: The 2022 edition of the Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Playoff’ brings back the shoe that Michael Jordan wore during his 1997 championship run. The mid-top sports an essential two-tone color scheme, featuring radiating stitched lines on the black leather upper and lizard-textured overlays in a contrasting white finish. The sneaker’s molded eyelets shine in metallic silver, while color-popped crimson accents land on the Jumpman-embroidered tongue and webbing heel loop. Performance benefits include full-length Zoom Air cushioning, a carbon fiber shank plate, and a rubber outsole with herringbone traction pods under the forefoot and heel.

name: Rick and Morty x MB.01
story: The Rick and Morty x PUMA MB.01 pays tribute to LaMelo Ball’s favorite Adult Swim program. The NBA athlete’s debut signature shoe features a mismatched design that pairs a neon green finish on the left shoe with a vibrant crimson finish on the right. The engineered mesh upper is marked with Rick and Morty branding atop the toe box, along with graphics inspired by the show on the lace guard. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a full-length Nitro Foam midsole.

name: Puma MB.01 LaMelo Ball Black Red Blast
Jordan 1 Retro High OG Dark Marina Blue
story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Dark Marina Blue’ dresses the iconic silhouette in classic two-tone color blocking. The all-leather upper features a black base with contrasting dark blue overlays along the forefoot, heel, collar and eyestay. A matching blue Swoosh is accompanied by a Jordan Wings logo stamped in black on the lateral collar flap. Atop the nylon tongue, a woven Nike Air tag nods to the shoe’s retro cushioning technology: an Air-sole unit encapsulated in polyurethane nestled in the heel of the rubber cupsole.

name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Dark Marina Blue (GS)
story: Built for big kids, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG GS ‘Dark Marina Blue’ dresses the classic silhouette in a simple two-tone color scheme. The leather upper combines a stealthy black base with contrasting blue overlays at the forefoot and heel. A woven Nike tag decorates the breathable nylon tongue, while a retro Wings logo embellishes the lateral collar flap. The high-top sits on a standard rubber cupsole, featuring an Air-sole heel unit encapsulated in a lightweight foam wedge.

name: Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70 Hi Todd Snyder Rebel Prep
Converse Jack Purcell Todd Snyder Rebel Prep
Yeezy Boost 350 V2 CMPCT 'Slate Red'
story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 CMPCT ‘Slate Red’ dresses the lifestyle sneaker in a saturated crimson hue that has become something of a design signature for Kanye West. The engineered Primeknit upper showcases an abstract woven pattern and a lacing system reminiscent of the Yeezy 450. Unlike the original 350 V2, this iteration features an elastic cuff for a snug, sock-like fit. Responsive cushioning is provided by a full-length Boost midsole, enveloped in a dark red rubber cage and supported by a color-matched rubber outsole.

name: Nike Dunk Low Valentine's Day (2021) (W)
story: The Nike women’s Dunk Low ‘Valentine's Day’ celebrates February 14 with frilly detailing and a vibrant color scheme. The low-top carries an upper constructed from textile twill in a rich Team Red hue. Tumbled leather overlays at the forefoot and heel are rendered in Pink Prime, while the color-matched hairy suede Swoosh is trimmed in pleated, translucent lace. The same burgundy and fuchsia hues up top are repeated on the durable rubber cupsole.

name: Jordan 5 Retro Racer Blue
story: The Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Racer Blue’ adds color-popped accents to a stealthy colorway of the venerable 1990 silhouette, designed by Tinker Hatfield and introduced to the world by Mars Blackmon. The mid-top makes use of a black nubuck upper with tonal TPU eyelets, translucent quarter panel netting and a reflective silver tongue. The latter features contrasting hits of royal blue on the embroidered Jumpman and interior lining. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a blue polyurethane midsole, embellished with black shark tooth detailing and fitted with visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel. A translucent rubber outsole provides grippy traction underfoot.

name: Union LA x Dunk Low 'Passport Pack - Psychic Blue'
Nike Dunk Low Union Passport Pack Grey Purple
story: The Union LA x Nike Dunk Low ‘Lakers’ showcases a combination of colors inspired by Los Angeles’ storied NBA franchise. The upper is constructed from semi-translucent ripstop textile that reveals a purple underlay on the toe box, quarter panel and collar. The same gridded design is applied to the forefoot and heel overlay, rendered in a solid white finish with contrast yellow stitching. More yellow stitching is applied to the patterned Swoosh, complete with excess hanging threads for a DIY-inspired look. A yellow ‘UN/LA’ tag decorates the quarter panel, while a circular emblem on the lateral heel displays the retailer’s OG Frontman logo. The distinctive silhouette makes a repeat appearance under the translucent purple rubber outsole.

name: Kanghyuk x Classic Leather 'White Primal Red'
Jordan 5 Low Arctic Pink (W)
story: The women’s Air Jordan 5 Retro Low ‘Girls That Hoop’ updates the classic silhouette with refreshed materials and colors. The low-top makes use of a pink nubuck upper with molded eyelets and OG plastic lace locks. A TPU grille reveals a reflective finish on the quarter panel underlay. The sneaker sits atop a red polyurethane midsole with black shark tooth detailing and a visible Air-sole unit in the heel. Underfoot, a translucent rubber outsole features a herringbone traction pattern for optimal grip.

Nike Blazer Low Acronym Night Maroon
story: The Acronym x Nike Blazer Low ‘Night Maroon’ presents Errolson Hugh’s modernist interpretation of Nike’s retro silhouette. The upper is constructed from burgundy textile with a vivid yellow Swoosh and distressed cut-away detailing throughout. A molded heel piece is riveted to the back of the low-top for an industrial aesthetic, while an exposed foam tongue connects the shoe to its vintage hardwood roots. The sneaker is mounted on a dark grey rubber midsole with a reinforced toe bumper.

Air Jordan 1 Mid SE TD 'Motorsport'
story: Built for little feet, the Air Jordan 1 Mid SE TD ‘Motorsport’ features a unique design inspired by Michael Jordan’s love of motorcycle racing. A subtle diamond texture is applied to the white synthetic leather upper, contrasted by forefoot and heel overlays in Gym Red and University Gold. On the sneaker’s lateral side, ‘23’ is stamped on the forefoot, while a red wings logo adorns the collar flap. A checkerboard Jordan decal embellishes the back heel. The mid-top sits on a standard rubber cupsole with Jordan branding on the lateral sidewall.
